Source: ebox-metapackages
Section: web
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ubuntu MOTU Developers <ubuntu-motu@lists.ubuntu.com>
XSBC-Original-Maintainer: Javier Uruen Val <javi@warp.es>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.7.3

Package: ebox-all
Architecture: all
Depends: ebox-gateway, ebox-security, ebox-infrastructure, ebox-office, ebox-communation
Description: eBox platform - all modules
 eBox is a framework for the development and deployment of security-wise
 network services in small and medium-sized networks, offering a simplified
 graphical interface to non expert users. It can be set up as a gateway,
 having some extra features over a usual router.
 .
 This metapackage installs all eBox modules.

Package: ebox-gateway
Architecture: all
Depends: ebox-network, ebox-trafficshaping, ebox-l7-protocols, ebox-firewall, ebox-squid, ebox-captiveportal, ebox-software
Description: eBox platform - gateway suite
 eBox is a framework for the development and deployment of security-wise
 network services in small and medium-sized networks, offering a simplified
 graphical interface to non expert users. It can be set up as a gateway,
 having some extra features over a usual router.
 .
 This metapackage installs typical modules for eBox acting as gateway.

